Frame‐by‐Frame Analysis:

• Frame 1: The dashcam (ego) is traveling in what appears to be the leftmost of two through‐lanes. A black SUV is clearly in the lane to the right. There is no additional paved lane visible beyond that SUV; to the right is a grassy shoulder and a sidewalk.

• Frame 3: The view is similar: still only one lane directly to the right, with no sign of further lanes.

Contextual Reasoning:
All five frames confirm there are only two lanes going in our direction—the one we’re in (left lane) and one to its immediate right. The area beyond the right lane is not a drivable lane but rather a shoulder/grass/sidewalk area.

Match to Answer Choices:
A: 5 lanes to the right – clearly not supported by the frames.  
B: 4 lanes to the right – no visual evidence of additional lanes beyond one.  
C: 3 lanes to the right – again, not seen; we only observe one.  
D: 2 lanes to the right – also incorrect, as there is only space for a single lane on the right.  
E: 1 lane to the right – matches what we see in every frame.
